Financial risk management objectives and policies (cont’d) Liquidity risk

Liquidity risk is the risk that the Group and the Company will not be able to meet their obligations as they fall due. Liquidity risk is managed by matching the payment and receipt cycle.

The Group and the Company monitor their liquidity risk and maintain a level of cash and bank balances deemed adequate by management to finance the Group‘s operations and to mitigate the effects of fluctuations in cash flows.

In view of the Group’s liquidity position and the liquidity risk management approach as described in Note 3(a), directors of the Company have a reasonable expectation that the Group and the Company have adequate resources to continue in operational existence for the foreseeable future.
